This paper deals with graph data mining, specifically the task of identifying dense bipartite subgraphs. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithms and computational complexity (cs.CC), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the context of graph mining. Finally, the implementation and experimentation aspects of the paper suggest a connection to databases (cs.DB).
